messageBody: Right!  I'd forgotten about the already-existing letter!  I didn't invent it, I simply re-purposed it.  So it seems less audacious of me to simply suggest the use of that letter as an alternate "L" for the purpose of making more connections!  Of course, since it's not strictly needed in my American English, all the arguments against it (mainly that it can be confused with "K"), still apply.  Oh well.
